Punjab
Sep 18, 2014
Murder, Dowry Harassment
Description:
			A local court sentenced three members of a family to life imprisonment in a dowry death case on Wednesday. Kuldeep Kaur of Saidoke village in Faridkot district was killed for dowry on September 30, 2012, by her husband and parents-in-laws at Karianwala village. Faridkot Sadar police had registered a case against the trio on the complaint of Kuldeep's father Beant Singh. District and sessions judge Archana Puri sentenced Kuldeep's husband Gurcharan Singh, father-in-law Darshan Singh and mother-in-law Mohinder Kaur to life imprisonment.